The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, May 18, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Tuesday, May 18, 2004				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Chaplin Square at 4.30 pm. A CPM victory procession will go around the CMC headquarters.				 																Workshops				 																																	A workshop on communication and soft skills, organised by Launcherz, at 110, Ashutosh Mukherjee Road, 11.30 am onwards.				 																																	A theatre workshop by The Infinity Company, Mumbai, at Baisakhi Apartments, 2, Deodhar Rahman Road, in Lake Gardens, 8 am. 				 																Bard tribute				 																																	Kabi Pranam, an evening of Tagore songs and recitation, presented by the government and Bhavna, at Eden Gardens Bandstand, 4.30 pm. Participants include Sunil Gangopadhyay, Soumitra Chatterjee, Swagatalakshmi Dasgupta, Rupa Ganguly and Srikanta Acharya. Jogesh Chandra Barman will release an audio album.				 																Talk				 																																	Surendra Munshi from IIMC will speak on Culture and management at The CMA-Patton Tuesday Talkshoppe at CMA Auditorium, Shakespeare Sarani, at 5.45 pm. 				 																Fun to learn				 																																	A folk painting workshop for children at Bharatiyam, from 10 am to 5 pm. Gond painting, kalamkari and Kalighat pata chitra will be taught. 				 																																	A summer crafts workshop for kids, conducted by Ranjan De, at Landmark, from 10.30 am to 2 pm.				 																Art beat				 																																	Summer Show, an all-India exhibition of paintings and sculptures at CIMA Gallery, 3 to 7 pm.
